# Architecture

## Layers

- **Routes** (`src/app/`) — thin pages; fetch data server-side, delegate to components
- **Server actions** (`src/actions/`) — mutations and authorized reads; always guard with `src/lib/authz.ts`
- **Services** (`src/services/`) — reusable business logic (CMS, settings)
- **Models** (`src/models/`) — Mongoose schemas only
- **Components** (`src/components/`) — UI; no direct DB access

## Auth

Use `requireAdmin()`, `requireRole()`, or `getAuthSession()` from `@/lib/authz` and `@/lib/session`. Do not duplicate `session?.user?.role !== "admin"` checks.

## Admin routes

Admin UI lives under `/admin/*`. Role dashboards stay at `/dashboard`. Lecturer tools at `/lecturer/*`.

## CMS

- Block types defined in `src/lib/content/types.ts` with Zod schemas
- Public rendering in `MarketingBlockRenderer` only — no business logic
- Settings (SEO, branding, theme) via `src/services/*-settings.ts` singleton docs

## Do not

- Put Mongoose calls in React components
- Hardcode tenant branding in shared admin chrome
- Add new marketing pages as static `page.tsx` files — use CMS + dynamic `[...slug]` route
